'API-driven image generation inside SaaS products'],
ARRAY['microsoft-365', 'zapier', 'slack', 'notion'],
'2026-06-13 00:00:00+00'),

-- 2. ZoomInfo - B2B intent and contact data head-term, peer-double for apollo S185/clearbit/6sense/demandbase S129
('zoominfo', 'ZoomInfo',
'B2B intent data and contact database with real-time buyer signals across millions of accounts.',
'ZoomInfo is the largest B2B contact and intent data platform on the market, listed on NASDAQ as ZI since 2020 with a coverage claim of more than 300 million professional contacts and over 100 million companies. The platform stitches together direct-dial phone numbers, verified email, org charts, technographic data (what tools each company uses), firmographic data, and proprietary intent topics that show which accounts are actively researching specific buying categories. SalesOS surfaces the contact and signal layer to AEs and SDRs, MarketingOS routes intent-qualified accounts into automation, OperationsOS pushes enriched data into Salesforce or HubSpot in real time, and Engage runs cadence sequences on top. The big tradeoffs are price (annual contracts only, no public pricing, entry deals run 15,000 to 30,000 USD per year for a small team) and contract lock-in via annual commits with hard renewal terms. Apollo competes on price and freemium access, Cognism on EU GDPR-compliant data, Clearbit (now HubSpot Breeze Intelligence) on enrichment depth. For an enterprise outbound team that needs the deepest dataset plus intent topics under one roof, ZoomInfo stays the category leader in 2026.',
'', 'https://www.zoominfo.com', 'https://www.zoominfo.com',
'paid', false, 1500, 4.4, 8200,
false, false, false,
