-- 3. Marketo Engage - Adobe enterprise marketing automation head-term, peer-double for activecampaign S189/hubspot S139/mailchimp S164/klaviyo S141
('marketo', 'Marketo Engage',
'Adobe enterprise marketing automation for B2B lead nurture, scoring, and journey orchestration.',
'Marketo was founded in 2006 by Phil Fernandez, went public in 2013, was taken private by Vista Equity in 2016 for 1.79 billion USD, and was acquired by Adobe in 2018 for 4.75 billion USD where it rebranded as Marketo Engage and joined the Experience Cloud. It is the default enterprise B2B marketing automation platform across mid-market and Fortune 500 marketing teams, designed around email-driven nurture campaigns, lead scoring models, account based marketing journeys, and revenue attribution. The Smart Campaigns workflow builder, lead scoring matrix, dynamic content rules, and integration with Adobe Analytics and Salesforce CRM are the differentiators that keep it in enterprise stacks despite the steep learning curve and high price (Growth tier starts around 1250 USD per month, Standard around 3200, Select and Prime tiers six figures annually). HubSpot competes downmarket on ease of use, Pardot (now Salesforce Marketing Cloud Account Engagement) competes within the Salesforce ecosystem, ActiveCampaign at a tenth of the price for SMB teams. For a B2B enterprise marketing team running multi-touch nurture campaigns at scale with Salesforce as the CRM of record, Marketo Engage remains the category default in 2026.',
'', 'https://business.adobe.com/products/marketo/adobe-marketo', 'https://business.adobe.com/products/marketo/adobe-marketo',
'paid', false, 1250, 4.3, 5400,
false, false, false,
