-- 4. Wistia - B2B video hosting peer-double for loom S167/heygen S159/synthesia S159/descript S141
('wistia', 'Wistia',
'Video hosting and analytics built for marketing teams that need data on every play.',
'Wistia is the video hosting platform that marketing teams choose when YouTube branding, distracting recommended videos, or shallow analytics will not work for the use case. Founded in 2006 in Cambridge Massachusetts and bootstrapped for over a decade before taking growth equity in 2017, Wistia built its product around three differentiators: a custom-branded player with no YouTube logos or recommendations, granular per-second heatmaps showing exactly which moments get rewatched and which get skipped, and lead capture forms (called Turnstile) that embed inside the video to gate the next chapter on email submission. The Soapbox screen recorder, Channels feature for serial video content, Live virtual event hosting, and native integrations with HubSpot, Marketo, Pardot, and Salesforce for play-data attribution round out the platform. Pricing is freemium: Free plan hosts 3 videos, Plus starts at 24 USD per month for 10 videos with light analytics, Pro at 99 USD adds heatmaps and Turnstile, Advanced at 399 USD covers larger libraries and SSO. Vidyard competes on sales team use cases (personal video recording at scale), Vimeo on creator and event hosting, Loom on async screen recording. For a marketing team where each play needs to drive a measurable next step, Wistia stays the cleanest pick in 2026.',
'', 'https://wistia.com', 'https://wistia.com',
'freemium', true, 24, 4.5, 1800,
false, false, false,
